to merge local into remote


create project in your local
git init --to initialise your local repo
git remote add origin <git repo url>
git add . --to staged your changes
git commit -m "commit comment" --to commit your changes into local repo
git push origin master //to commit changes into remote repo

to cloning project into your local from remote
create a folder in your local
git clone <git remote url>

to pull the changes from remote--
one cloning is done.
go to project path.
git pull origin master

how to do pull request and branching and merging
create branch in remote
go to your project and open your bash or command prompt
git pull origin <branch name>
git checkout <branch name>
git branch-->it should point to new branch now
